HEADWORD: Miche
<hw>Miche</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v.
i.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>michen</ets>; cf. OE. <ets>muchier</ets>,
<ets>mucier</ets>, to conceal, F. <ets>musser</ets>, and OHG.
<ets>m⟦umac⟧hhen</ets> to waylay. Cf. <er>Micher</er>,
<er>Curmudgeon</er>, <er>Muset</er>.]</ety> <def>To lie hid; to skulk;
to act, or carry one's self, sneakingly.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Colloq.]</mark> <altsp>[Written also <asp>meach</asp> and
<asp>meech</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

